nder.","Assemble the seals onto the piston.","Spring","Valve cap","Valve spring","Valve","Primary cup seal","Piston","Piston retaining pin","Secondary cup seal","Rubber boot","Push rod","If removed, install the valve, valve spring and valve cover.","Lubricate the piston, seals and cylinder with new, clean brake fluid.","Fit the new spring and piston assembly into the master cylinder, aligning the retaining pin hole with the hole in the master cylinder body.","Install the piston retaining pin.","Piston retaining pin","Master cylinder","Lubricate the seal for the hose inlet spigot with new, clean brake fluid. Install the seal and the hose inlet spigot. ","Hose inlet spigot","Seal","Master cylinder","Bleed Screw","Assemble the cover onto the bleed screw thread.","Install the bleed screw and tighten to ","8 Nm",".","Master cylinder","Bleed screw","Cover","Brake Lever","Install the span adjuster pivot and the span adjuster into the lever.","Lever","Detent assembly","Circlip","Span adjuster","Span adjuster pivot","Install the circlip to retain the span adjuster.","Do not install the detent assembly at this stage as there is insufficient clearance on the support piece of","service tool T3880636",".","Position the lever pivot assembly and the spring as noted during disassembly.","Locate the pivot sleeve over the shank of the installer piece of ","service tool T3880636",".","Pivot sleeve","Installer piece","Mandrel","Screw the installer piece into the mandrel.","Align the brake lever to the brake lever pivot assembly ensuring the return spring is located as noted during removal.","Using the service tool, align the installer piece to the brake lever and gently push down on the mandrel to locate the installer piece, through the lever and pivot.","Place the lower surface of the brake lever onto the support piece, and then using a press, push the pivot sleeve through the brake lever pivot until the mandrel touches the upper brake lever surface.","Mandrel","Support piece","Lever"